.TH "cs4270_soc_put_mute" 9 "cs4270_soc_put_mute" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cs4270_soc_put_mute \- put callback for the 'Master Playback switch' alsa control.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cs4270_soc_put_mute
.BI "(struct snd_kcontrol *kcontrol "  ","
.BI "struct snd_ctl_elem_value *ucontrol "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kcontrol" 12
mixer control
.IP "ucontrol" 12
control element information
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function basically passes the arguments on to the generic
\fBsnd_soc_put_volsw\fP function and saves the mute information in
our private data structure. This is because we want to prevent
\fBcs4270_dai_mute\fP neglecting the user's decision to manually
mute the codec's output.

Returns 0 for success.
